Governor Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom state has signed the 2020 Appropriation bill of N597.735billion into Law. The state House of Assembly had on December 5, 2019, passed the N597.735billion budget estimate for the 2020 fiscal year as against the proposed N597.800 billion budget presented to them by the state Governor on October 8, 2019. This is made up of N111.250 billion for recurrent expenditure, N369.577 billion for Capital expenditure and N116. 934 billion for Consolidated Revenue Fund Charges. Speaker of Akwa Ibom state House of Assembly, Mr. Aniekan Bassey was present during the brief ceremony held at the Government House Uyo. Also present were all members of the State Executive Council including the Commissioner of Finance Mr. Linus Nkan, state Attorney General and Commissioner for Justice, Mr. Uwemedimo Nwoko. The 2020 budget is christened ‘The Budget of Industrialisation for Poverty Alleviation phase 2’, and according to the governor was designed as a key milestone in actualizing his completion agenda. VANGUARD BY: Chioma Onuegbu - Uyo Governor Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom state has proposed a total budget estimate of N 597, 800 for the 2020 fiscal year before the state House of Assembly. This is made up of N111.225billion for Recurrent Expenditure, N369.642 billion for Capital Expenditure. and N116.933billion as… October 8, 2019 In "Finance" GOVERNOR Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom State has signed the N646.6 billion 2018 budget passed last Tuesday by the state House of Assembly into Law. February 22, 2018 In "News" Uyo—GOVERNOR Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom has proposed a  budget estimate of N670.718 billion for the 2019 fiscal year. November 15, 2018 In "News"